Glom (Verb)


Meaning- To glom is to take or get something.
                  - most often used in the phrase “glom on to” to refer to taking something for your own use 
             
Example- The book consists of a collection of humorous essays glommed from popular magazines.
 That author is known for glomming on to other people's ideas as if they were his own.

Pronunciation-  How to pronounce GLOM in English (cambridge.org)
